### Adjusting themes


\index{ggplot2!theme\_minimal} \index{ggplot2!theme} \index{ggplot2!element\_text}
\index{ggtext!element\_textbox\_simple} \index{ggplot2!element\_blank} \index{ggplot2!element\_rect}

overlaying legend add outline box to distinguish between points on chart, and points in legend






::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
text_plot +
  theme_minimal(base_family = body_font, base_size = 6.5) +
  theme(
    # legend styling
    legend.position = "inside",
    legend.position.inside = c(0.9, 0.25),
    legend.background = element_rect(
      fill = alpha(bg_col, 0.6),
      color = text_col
    ),
    # text
    text = element_text(color = text_col),
    plot.title = element_text(
      family = title_font,
      face = "bold",
      size = rel(1.5)
    ),
    plot.subtitle = ggtext::element_textbox_simple(),
    plot.caption = ggtext::element_textbox_simple(),
    plot.title.position = "plot",
    plot.caption.position = "plot",
    # background and grid
    plot.margin = margin(5, 5, 5, 5),
    panel.grid.minor = element_blank(),
    plot.background = element_rect(
      fill = bg_col,
      color = bg_col
    ),
    panel.background = element_rect(
      fill = bg_col,
      color = bg_col
    )
  )
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![Bubble plot of the relationship between the age of pet cats and the average amount of time they spend indoors. The text is now all correctly formatted, and the legend appears inset with a clear border between it and the plot.](cats_files/figure-pdf/fig-cats-styled-plot-1.pdf){#fig-cats-styled-plot fig-pos='H'}
